Tic-Tac-Toe Game 🎮

This is a simple Tic-Tac-Toe game built using Python and Tkinter, providing a graphical user interface (GUI) for an interactive experience. The game allows two players to compete against each other in a classic 3x3 Tic-Tac-Toe match.

📥 Download & Run

Mac Users

Download the game from the GitHub Releases.

Unzip the file if it is compressed.

Run the game:

If you see a security warning, right-click on TicTacToe.app, select "Open", and approve the execution.

Alternatively, go to System Preferences → Security & Privacy → General and click "Allow Anyway".

Windows Users

Download the executable from the GitHub Releases.

Run TicTacToe.exe (No installation required!).

If Windows Defender blocks it, click "More Info" → "Run Anyway".

Run from Source Code (For Developers)

If you prefer to run the game from the Python source code:

Install Python (if not already installed) from python.org.

Clone this repository:

git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/TicTacToe.git
cd TicTacToe

Run the game:

python TicTacToe.py

🛠️ Features

✅ Simple and interactive GUI using Tkinter
✅ Two-player gameplay
✅ Winning combinations detection
✅ Restart button to play again
✅ Lightweight and easy to run

Enjoy the game! 🎉
                
